Shoot Command

Let's say you have to shoot something 10 times in 20 sec.
Each time you shoot it, an attribute on the object is increased by one.
```
object.shots = object.shots + 1
SetTimeout (20) {
  if (object.shots >= 20) {
    msg ("You win.")
  }
  else {
    msg ("You lose.")
  }
}
Not a great coder so this is where I'd start.
